2018-04-10T15:47:23Z", "closed_at": "2018-04-10T15:47:23Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "body_html": "<p>PyTorch master</p>\n<p>Currently, indexing a tensor by a zero-dim tensor creates a copy. We should make it return an alias.</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre>idx <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.tensor(<span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>, <span class=\"pl-v\">dtype</span><span class=\"pl-k\">=</span>torch.int64)\nx <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.arange(<span class=\"pl-c1\">9</span>).reshape(<span class=\"pl-c1\">3</span>, <span class=\"pl-c1\">3</span>)\nx[idx].zero_()   <span class=\"pl-c\"><span class=\"pl-c\">#</span> no effect since x[idx] copies; it should slice instead</span>\n<span class=\"pl-c1\">print</span>(x)</pre></div>\n<pre><code> 0  1  2\n 3  4  5\n 6  7  8\n[torch.FloatTensor of size (3,3)]\n</code></pre>\n<p>Reported by lvdmaaten</p>", "body_text": "PyTorch master\nCurrently, indexing a tensor by a zero-dim tensor creates a copy. We should make it return an alias.\nidx = torch.tensor(0, dtype=torch.int64)\nx = torch.arange(9).reshape(3, 3)\nx[idx].zero_()   # no effect since x[idx] copies; it should slice instead\nprint(x)\n 0  1  2\n 3  4  5\n 6  7  8\n[torch.FloatTensor of size (3,3)]\n\nReported by lvdmaaten", "body": "PyTorch master\r\n\r\nCurrently, indexing a tensor by a zero-dim tensor creates a copy. We should make it return an alias.\r\n\r\n```python\r\nidx = torch.tensor(0, dtype=torch.int64)\r\nx = torch.arange(9).reshape(3, 3)\r\nx[idx].zero_()   # no effect since x[idx] copies; it should slice instead\r\nprint(x)\r\n```\r\n\r\n```\r\n 0  1  2\r\n 3  4  5\r\n 6  7  8\r\n[torch.FloatTensor of size (3,3)]\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nReported by lvdmaaten"}